<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E3CFFB248A7512AFE0CF85A" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418E3CFFB248A7512AFC97F876" blockId="114.[151,1438,1542,2034]" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E3CFFB248A7512AFE32F9EF" bold="true" box="[151,407,1542,1567]" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48E3CFFB24A87512AFCE1F9EE" box="[695,836,1542,1566]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0999999999999996" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" unit="mm" value="3.0999999999999996" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="2.8">2.8-3.4 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible testaceous; antenna testaceous or brown; mesosoma and metasoma black; legs testaceous, except metacoxae basally black. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 12:7:9:7:7:8:8:9:9:10. Head shiny, punctate, unsculptured among punctures, with more or less numerous areolae mainly near orbits; frontal line complete; face with two longitudinal keels around orbits directed towards antennal toruli; occipital carina complete; POL = 7; OL = 3; OOL = 7; OPL = 3; TL = 3.5. Scutum, scutellum and metanotum shiny, smooth, finely punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Notauli incomplete, reaching approximately 0.5 length of scutum. Propodeum reticulate rugose, with strong transverse keel between dorsal and posterior surface; posterior surface with two longitudinal keels, median area shiny and smooth and lateral areas rugose. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; distal part of stigmal vein shorter than proximal part (3:10); marginal cell open. Paramere (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E3CFFB24C015066FB06F892" box="[1073,1187,1866,1890]" captionStart="PLATE 30" captionStartId="113.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[182,1402,234,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-92@113.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="113" captionText="PLATE 30. A, B. Chelae, holotypes. C–E. Male genitalia. A. Anteon hunanense (from Xu et al. 2012c). B. A. indicum (from Olmi 1984). C. A. ingenuum, holotype (from Olmi 1984). D. A. insertum, paratype (from Olmi 1991). E. A. isoneuron, holotype (from Xu et al. 1998). Scale bar 0.29 mm for A, 0.17 mm for B, 0.18 mm for C, 0.19 mm for D and 0.20 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278478/files/figure.png" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">Plate 30C</figureCitation>
) without distal inner process and dorsal membranous process. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E3CFFB248F750BFFE0CF85A" blockId="114.[151,1438,1542,2034]" box="[199,425,1938,1963]" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E3CFFB248F750BFFE80F85B" bold="true" box="[199,293,1939,1963]" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
